{"word":"H2930 - טָמֵא - ṭâmêʼ - taw-may' - Defile","slug":"H2930","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">טָמֵא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ṭâmêʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>taw-may'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Defile"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D8;&#x05DE;&#x05D0; - t&#x0323;a&#x0302;me&#x0302;'</b> - <i>taw-may'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be foul</i>, especially in a ceremonial or moral sense (<i>contaminated</i>): - defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, X utterly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2931\">H2931</a>, <a href=\"#/H2932\">H2932</a>"}]}